    "The β-VAE spatial modes are defined as the result of using the β-VAE decoder network with an input vector, s i, containing a unit value in the desired i th element and zero elsewhere, s i = δ j i = ð0, Á Á Á,1, Á Á Á,0Þ, that gives as a result the corresponding spatial i th mode.",
    "For a detailed description, the reader is referred to the Methods section.",
    "The reconstructed energy in this case is equal to E = 97.5%, with a cross correlation coefficient, R 12 = 0.0015.",
    "It is observed from Fig. 1c, d that the spatial modes obtained from both methods exhibit the same pattern of shedding flow.",
    "The spectrum of the temporal coefficients for both methods is shown in the last column of Fig. 1c, d."
